0. Prerequisite

  * Ubuntu (preferably >= 11.04)


Host/Guest machine preparation
==============================

1. Install necessary packages to both host machines

  $ sudo aptitude -R install qemu-kvm		# for qemu/kvm
  $ sudo aptitude -R install python-vm-builder	# for vmbuilder
  $ sudo aptitude -R rsync

2. Generate an SSH key pair that root @ guest will accept

  $ ssh-keygen -t rsa -N "" -f id_rsa_vm

3. Create a virtual machine image with a guest OS installed (this takes around 11 minutes)

  $ sudo vmbuilder kvm ubuntu --rootsize=1024 --swapsize=0 --ssh-key=id_rsa_vm.pub --addpkg=openssh-server --addpkg=rsync --addpkg=psmisc --addpkg=libprotobuf6 --hostname=guest --user=xia --pass=xia --rootpass=xia --suite=natty

4. Prepare a bridge

  If /etc/network/interfaces contained the following:

auto eth0
iface eth0 inet dhcp
  hwaddress ether ...

  Replace it with the following:

auto br0
iface br0 inet dhcp
  hwaddress ether ...
  bridge_ports eth0
  post-up brctl setageing br0 0  # always broadcast

  $ sudo ifup br0


Click on host
=============

1. Build click on a host machine (as referred in common.sh)

  $ ./configure --enable-userlevel
  $ make -j24

2. Execute click

  $ ./run_host_click.sh


Click on guest
==============

1. Load KVM (not required but better for performance)

  $ sudo modprobe kvm-intel

2. Power on the guest

  $ ./start_local_guest.sh

3. Copy click to the guest and run it (after the guest is powered on)

  $ ./run_guest_click.sh


Click on client
===============

1. Run ping client

 $ sudo userlevel/click conf/xia/xia_ping_client.click


Live migration
==============
1. Begin migration from A to B (can be executed on any host)

  $ ./migrate_to_hostB.sh

2. Begin migration from B to A (can be executed on any host)

  $ ./migrate_to_hostA.sh

